        "text": "The book title of Luhmann's last major work, *Die Gesellschaft der Gesellschaft* (The Society of Society), quite deliberately flaunts this circularity, but at its core the first major work, *Soziale Systeme. Grundriß einer allgemeinen Theorie*, says nothing else: Theories with a claim to universality are easily recognized by the fact that they themselves appear as their own object. Universality of the subject areas in the sense that as a sociological theory it treats everything social and not only sections (such as stratification and mobility, characteristics of modern society, patterns of interaction, etc.)."
