      "type": "edit",
      "id": "89f7b49c65a5d08d",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "89f7b49c65a5d08d",
        "text": "The book title of Luhmann's last major work, *Die Gesellschaft der Gesellschaft* (The Society of Society), quite deliberately flaunts this circularity, but at its core the first major work, *Soziale Systeme. Grundriß einer allgemeinen Theorie*, says nothing else: theories with claims to universality are easily recognized by the fact that they themselves appear as their own subject matter. Universality of subject matter in the sense that, as a sociological theory, it deals with everything social and not just sub-areas (such as stratification and mobility, features of modern society, patterns of interaction, etc.)."
      },
