      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "03ec1b661a598a5a",
        "text": "And also in the magnificent, recently published, comprehensive work *Die Systemtheorie der Gesellschaft* (The Systems Theory of Society) from his estate, Luhmann points out that the claim to a \"general theory of social systems\" implies precisely that \"sociology can also conceive of itself as a subsystem of society\" (Luhmann 2017, p. 12 f.). This is consequential for a systems-theoretical conception of the media, which grasps mass media as a \"condition of the possibility of modern society\" (Luhmann 1997, p. 883 f.) and thus at the same time counts among the conditions of possibility of the systems theory of society."
