    {
      "type": "add",
      "id": "f6d0b940fc702742",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "f6d0b940fc702742",
        "text": "All three of these works are certainly not \"key works of media studies,\" but for the topic of media, two things emerge from the basic theoretical arrangement: 1) Media, insofar as they are to be counted as part of the social, must be dealt with by systems theory. 2) Insofar as media (language, writing, letterpress, mass media, cf. Luhmann 2017, p. 883) belong to the preconditions of society that sociology describes, the relations are also to be 'thought circularly' in this case."
