        "id": "86b61c95cf3bd4f4",
        "text": "The reality of mass media continues after this first sentence with two more impositions. One is meant for the subject. Luhmann clarifies: \"This also applies to sociologists, who can no longer gain their knowledge by strolling around, nor with their naked eyes and ears. Especially when they apply the so-called empirical methods, they always already know what they know and what they do not know - from the mass media\" (Luhmann 1996, p. 9, footnote 1)."
